'''''-n''''' is a [[Quenya]] suffix that has three meanings.

==-n<sup>1</sup>==
Used as a dative ending to indicate the indirect object of a sentence. For example in '''''nin''''' "for me" <ref>{{Cite DTP|LR 2.08.079}}</ref> and <nowiki>'''</nowiki>'''''enyalien''''' "in memory of".<ref>{{UT|8c}}</ref>

==-n<sup>2</sup>==
'''-n''' or '''-nye''' is a pronominal ending, 1st person singular "I". It is used to indicate an action is being completed by the speaker.  For example, '''-n''' is used as a modifier in ''Elendil's Oath,'' to form '''''utúlien''''' "I am come" from  '''''utúlie''''' "has come".<ref>{{RK|VI5}}, p. 967</ref> <ref>{{webcite|author=Paul Strack|articleurl=https://eldamo.org/content/words/word-2588932767.html?neo|articlename=Q. tul-|website=Eldamo|accessed=17 May 2025}}</ref>

==-n<sup>3</sup>==
Used as a plural sign used of the cases.<ref>{{WJ|Quendi}}, p. 407</ref>{{examples}}

